text.1: A 29 yo male presented with 6 months of progressive painless lesions, with no systemic symptoms. Biopsy showed diffuse dermal infiltrate, blast-like cells extending to the hypodermis. Immunohistochemical analysis tested positive for CD4, CD56 & CD123. What is the diagnosis?
text.2: The NEJM Clinical Cases Resource Center aggregates interactive cases and educational resources developed specifically for teaching, continuous learning, and professional development.
text.3: A 72 yo woman who, 25 years prior, had mechanical mitral & aortic valves replaced presented to the hospital with weakness & dark urine. Cardiac ultrasonography revealed normal biventricular function, no pericardial effusion & a possible clot. Diagnostic tests were performed.
